FIG. 3.
Immunohistochemistry for GFP-tagged tumor cells in an explant ovarian cancer cell adhesion assay. (A) GFP-tagged DOV13 ovarian cancer cells or multicellular aggregates (MCAs) were incubated with a murine parietal peritoneum explant and allowed to adhere for 2h. After rinsing, samples were fixed with 10% formalin and processed for histology. IHC for GPF reveals cells and MCAs in contact with peritoneal collagen. (B) Schematic of parietal peritoneum and ovarian cancer cell adhesion is given as a reference. Asterisk indicates area of sections that consist of peritoneal collagen (predominantly type I), which is found directly under the mesothelium and is between 10 and 40μm thick in mice. Scale bars equal 50 μm.
