FIG. 8.
In situ zymography of gelatinase activity in xenograft ovarian tumor. The presence of gelatinase activity in cryosectionsfrom SKOV3 ovarian cancer xenograft tumors was assessed with in situ zymography using FITC-conjugated DQ-gelatin as described. Cleavage of the quenched fluorescent gelatin reveals the FITC signal. Tissues were snap frozen in isopentane cooled by liquid nitrogen. Original magnification of image was 200 ×.
